[02:09:29] # Veggie Lo Mein

**Servings:** 4 | **Prep Time:** 5 minutes | **Cook Time:** 15 minutes

---

## Sauce

- 1/3 cup reduced-sodium tamari (or reduced-sodium soy sauce, or coconut aminos)
- 1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger
- 1 tablespoon honey (or pure maple syrup to make it vegan)
- 1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil
- 2 teaspoons sriracha

## Noodles & Vegetables

- 8 ounces whole-wheat spaghetti
- 1 tablespoon olive or avocado oil
- 1 (3.5-ounce) package shiitake mushrooms (stemmed and thinly sliced)
- 1 red bell pepper (seeded and thinly sliced)
- 1 cup grated carrots
- 3 cloves garlic (minced)
- 3 cups chopped broccoli florets
- 1 cup snow peas
- 1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt (plus more to taste)
- Sliced green onions (for garnish)

---

## Instructions

1. **Cook the noodles:** Bring a large pot of salted water to a rapid boil. Cook the spaghetti until just shy of al dente (about 1–2 minutes less than package directions), typically 7 to 10 minutes. Drain, reserving about 1/4 cup of pasta water in case the finished dish needs loosening. Set noodles aside.

2. **Make the sauce:** While the spaghetti cooks, whisk together the 1/3 cup tamari, 1 tablespoon ginger, 1 tablespoon honey, 1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil, and 2 teaspoons sriracha in a small bowl. Set aside.

3. **Stir-fry the vegetables:** Heat the 1 tablespoon olive or avocado oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add the shiitake mushrooms, red bell pepper, 1 cup grated carrots, and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently, until tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Add the 3 cups broccoli florets and 1 cup snow peas, toss to combine, and season with the 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cook for another 2 to 3 minutes, until broccoli is crisp-tender and bright green.

4. **Combine:** Add the drained noodles and all the sauce to the skillet. Toss everything together over medium heat for about 1 minute until the noodles are well coated and heated through. If the mixture looks dry or sticky, splash in a little rese
